  "prompt": "How can I delete a Google account from my phone?",
  "response": "To delete a Google account from your phone, the steps differ slightly depending on whether you have an Android or iPhone:\n\nFor Android:\n1. Go to \"Settings\"\n2. Tap \"Accounts\" or \"Users & Accounts\"\n3. Select the Google account you want to remove\n4. Tap \"Remove account\"\n5. Confirm by tapping \"Remove account\" again\n\nFor iPhone:\n1. Go to \"Settings\"\n2. Scroll down and tap \"Gmail\" or \"Google\"\n3. Tap \"Remove Account\"\n4. Confirm by tapping \"Delete from My iPhone\"\n\nNote: Removing the account will delete all Google-related data from your phone, including emails, contacts, and calendar events synced with that account.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
